news.title: Over 95% buildings in Bengaluru violated norms: ACCE India
news.para: Shrikant S Channal, chairman of the association, termed the situation ‘dangerous’ and urged BBMP and the government to act immediately to prevent shoddy constructions and rectify flaws in existing ones.

news.title: Star Housing expects 10-15% of business from semi urban locations in next three years
news.para: ​There has been an uptick in demand fueled by the migration from small hamlets to semi-urban areas and reverse migration from cities to these locations, Star Housing Finance (Star HFL) said in a release.

news.title: DDA to launch new housing scheme, offer nearly 15,000 flats
news.para: The flats of different categories located at Dwarka, Narela, Rohini and Jasola, among other places will be offered under this scheme and are those which remained "unsold in previous housing schemes" of the urban body, the DDA said in a statement.

news.title: M3M acquires 30-acre land in Gurugram for Rs 350 crore
news.para: "Under the Deen Dayal Jan Awas Yojana, we will invest another Rs 1,000 crore to create 2,000 independent floors," M3M India director PankajBansal said. "We will launch this initiative within this financial year."

news.title: ArcelorMittal Nippon Steel leases office space in BKC for India headquarters
news.para: AM/NS India, which is 60% owned by the world’s biggest steelmaker and the rest by Japan’s Nippon Steel, has leased over 45,000 sq ft office space in Raheja Towers for a tenure of five years.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP asks nine builders not to charge buyers disproportionately
news.para: DTCP found that most of the projects are running behind schedule and their licences have expired. Teams from the department also found that construction work had stopped at some sites and very few workers were deployed.

news.title: Centre to repeal Delhi Rent Control act, soon to bring a new law for the capital
news.para: Though officials didn’t divulge about the provisions that the proposed bill will have, going by the government’s stand so far it will be in complete alignment with the Model Act that the Centre has approved.

news.title: Unitech promoter's wife hid association with a host of companies: ED
news.para: The ED has alleged that earlier this year, when Preeti Chandra was questioned a few times and asked about details of her association with companies and other financial transactions, she claimed to be associated with only four companies.

news.title: Salarpuria Sattva to take over part of Cloudtail business
news.para: The new company, Bengaluru-based Dawntech Electronics, is the first such independent well-funded preferred seller that is getting the business of Cloudtail, which earlier this year announced that it would wind up operations by next May.

news.title: Sundaram high yield secured real estate fund III to raise Rs 750 crore
news.para: Karthik Athreya, head of strategy, Alternate Credit, said that the funds have risk mitigation strategies that are differentiated in the market in terms of underwriting methods and diligence focus.

news.title: All unregistered projects stayed by Delhi REAT
news.para: The Real Estate Appellate Tribunal noted that even though builders are covered under the Rera Act, several projects have been constructed without seeking the mandatory registration.

news.title: SC re-imposes ban on construction activities in Delhi-NCR
news.para: A bench headed by Chief Justice N.V. Ramana and comprising Justices D.Y. Chandrachud and Surya Kant said: "In the meantime, as an interim measure and until further orders, we re-impose the ban on the construction activities in the NCR."

news.title: Country's housing market at higher risk of correction: Bank of Canada
news.para: Paul Beaudry, in a virtual speech to a provincial regulator, also said Canada's main financial system vulnerabilities - housing market imbalances and high levels of household debt - had been intensified by the pandemic.

news.title: ITC Hotel goes aggressive in new properties rollout
news.para: ​ITC Hotels is pursuing an 'asset right' strategy while simultaneously leveraging ITC's world class properties to drive growth, the official said.

news.title: Virtual real estate plot sells for record $2.4 million
news.para: Decentraland is an online environment - also called a "metaverse" - where users can buy land, visit buildings, walk around and meet people as avatars.
